    {
      "id": "3b0c2042_f8bffa72",
      "file_path": "controlloop/common/eventmanager/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/controlloop/eventmanager/ControlLoopEventManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 181,
      "message": "this particular method was cloned, thus unchanged.  However, your question is a valid one.  When I wrote the original code from which it was cloned, I assumed that the overall control loop timeout superseded the individual operations.  Is that not a correct assumption?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-08-20 16:50:36.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "88d23ce3_2d2ce681",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "6194b467_cf0cf8a3",
      "file_path": "controlloop/common/eventmanager/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/controlloop/eventmanager/ControlLoopEventManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 181,
      "message": "I think that would be the expected behavior.   I don't think though that there are any checks across these fields neither in clamp nor policy that the aggregate of the timeout values for the individual operations, and the overall one are somewhat consistent (would be up to the designer to ensure that make sense).    If we were to do something about it, I agree it would be out of the scope of this work.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
